 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Destruction Warlock Phase 1 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 390 top-ranked Destruction Warlock DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 1 (Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Destruction Warlock items in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Spellstrike Pants (87%), Voidheart Mantle (81%), Voidheart Crown (78%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Destruction Warlock use in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Chaotic Skyfire Diamond in the meta socket, then Veiled Noble Topaz and Glowing Nightseye in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Destruction Warlock need in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Power on head, Greater Inscription of Discipline on shoulders, Runic Spellthread on legs and Enchant Weapon - Sunfire on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Power comes from Almaador — Shattrath City."
  }
